Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2015 17:36:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 406/429] i2c_pmic: remove driver from kernel config
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The i2c_pmic driver is not needed for the EDISON hardware, and
it generates interrupts that prevents the platform to remain
in suspend to ram (S3) state.

Signed-off-by: Lo√Øc Akue <loicx.akue@intel.com>
---
 arch/x86/configs/i386_edison_defconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/configs/i386_edison_defconfig b/arch/x86/configs/i386_edison_defconfig
index d186936bc366..049b900651aa 100644
--- a/arch/x86/configs/i386_edison_defconfig
+++ b/arch/x86/configs/i386_edison_defconfig
@@ -1545,7 +1545,7 @@ CONFIG_I2C_DESIGNWARE_CORE_FORK=y
 CONFIG_I2C_DESIGNWARE_PCI_FORK=y
 # CONFIG_I2C_DESIGNWARE_PLATFORM_FORK is not set
 CONFIG_I2C_DW_SPEED_MODE_DEBUG=y
-CONFIG_I2C_PMIC=y
+# CONFIG_I2C_PMIC is not set
 # CONFIG_I2C_DESIGNWARE_PCI is not set
 # CONFIG_I2C_EG20T is not set
 CONFIG_I2C_GPIO=y
